                            <h3 class="entry-title"><a href="#">COOKING IT!! YOUR DREAM KITCHEN ON A BUDGET </a></h3>
                            <div class="date">31.01.2022</div>
                            <p>

                                Often as much a space for socializing, relaxing and dinning, as it is for cooking and clearing up, today’s kitchen plays an important role as the hub of the home. There are so many considerations, mention a huge range of option on offer, so it’s easy to get carried away and have cost spiral out of control. But some careful planning is all it takes to achieve the kitchen of your dreams at the amount of money you want to spend.
So how to begin? Consider which items are essential ‘’for example do you have your heart on set on a steam oven or a boiling water tap? Are u Imaging a solid wood breakfast bar, or is storage the key focus? Then you can begin to pave down other elements you may not need and keep your budget in check while every project is, of course, different depending upon room size and specification, the furniture usually consists the largest part of a new kitchen’s expenditure. Follow by worktops and appliances and then, finally the cost of fitting. However, don’t cut corners here, because a high-quality fit with attention to details will help your kitchen make maximum impact.</p><br>
                            <h3>Furniture finds </h3>
                            <p>Many kitchen retailers will offer a range of furniture at different price points, allowing you to choose a design to suit the budget. Lower price rate may have more fixed choices, in term of available colors and sizes, and more affordable carcasses. Look at the latest material and innovation, reasonably priced laminate and foiled wrapped doors offer extra ordinary realistic, hard wearing timber effects and textured options, be upfronts about what you are willing to spend, don’t comprised on quality, whatever your budget. Your kitchen is an investment that should be considered carefully, to ensure it will suit your needs many more years to come.
                                The layout of the room is very important to a successful outcome.it is vital that storage, preparation, cooking and washing up areas are within easy reach of each other. One way to keep cost down is to work with the position of existing power and water supplies. As these can be very expensive to move, planning is the key don’t be tempted to fill every void with furniture, you may find it you need fewer cabinmates if you plan your storage carefully and optimize space with full outs and internal fittings.
                                </p><br>

                                <h3>Surface matters </h3>
                                <p>Worktops are also important consideration wood and laminate worktops tend to be more affordable than quartz, solid surface and national stone. But ultra-durable than quartz and proclaim materials, or solid surface with its joint free look, may offer more design freedom not to mention their great stain resistance and ease maintenance. Technical advances also mean many of these man-made surface offer authentic and beautiful looking marble and other stone effects. The growth in popularity of premium quartz is in part, due to the materials ability to deliver a long lasting and luxurious look to any kitchen design, making it well worth the investment, when occupied with other carefully considered flourishes, it can help make even the most cost effective off the shelf solution look for more expensive.
                                    </p><br>
                                    <h3>Cooking it </h3>
                                    <p>When it comes to appliances, there is plenty of choice most quality manufacture ranges at different price points. Entry-level models will usually have the same quality but few features -so it is worth considering the way you like to cook, the amount of chilled and frozen food storage you require and just how feature rich an appliance you need its worth factoring in how long you expect your appliances to last. If you prefer to buy a less premium model, don’t forget most inbuilt in appliances comes in standard sizes, so you can up spec at at a later date when you budget permits.
                                        It’s in the detail 
                                        Before going ahead with your chosen kitchen company, take the time to ensure there are no unpleasant cost surprises ahead. The designer should plan and elevation of the proposed design and detailed quotation listing the style, construction, finishes, materials, appliances and a precise description of everything included. The should also give you a cost breakdown to demonstrate how they have reached their fee and what it includes and excludes 
                                        
